1️⃣ Reverse String — Interview Style
Write a method reverseString(String input)
Return the reversed string without using StringBuilder.reverse().


2️⃣ Compare Two Strings
Write a method isEqual(String s1, String s2)
Return true if both strings are same (case-sensitive).
Another version: compare ignoring case.


3️⃣ Find Substring
Write a method getSubstring(String str, int start, int end)
Return substring between given indexes.
Test with: "AutomationTesting"


4️⃣ Count Words in a String
Given: "Selenium automation with Java"
Write a method to count number of words.


5️⃣ Check Palindrome String
Write a method isPalindrome(String str)
Return true if string reads same backward & forward.
(Interview favorite)


6️⃣ Count Occurrence of a Character
Input: "automation" and 'a'
Count how many times 'a' appears.


7️⃣ Remove Spaces From String
Given "Selenium Testing"
Remove all spaces → "SeleniumTesting".


8️⃣ Print Only Unique Characters
Input: "programming"
Output characters that appear once.


9️⃣ Find Duplicate Characters
Input: "testautomation"
Print all duplicate letters.